data[0][text]: 1. I have saved up so many things that they get in the way.
data[1][text]: 2. I check things more often than necessary.
data[2][text]: 3. I get upset if objects are not arranged properly.
data[3][text]: 4. I feel compelled to count while I am doing things.
data[4][text]: 5. I find it difficult to touch an object when I know it has been touched by strangers or certain people.
data[5][text]: 6. I find it difficult to control my own thoughts.
data[6][text]: 7. I collect things I don't need.
data[7][text]: 8. I repeatedly check doors, windows, drawers, etc.
data[8][text]: 9. I get upset if others change the way I have arranged things.
data[9][text]: 10. I feel I have to repeat certain numbers.
data[10][text]: 11. I sometimes have to wash or clean myself simply because I feel contaminated.
data[11][text]: 12. I am upset by unpleasant thoughts that come into my mind against my will.
data[12][text]: 13. I avoid throwing things away because I am afraid I might need them later.
data[13][text]: 14. I repeatedly check gas and water taps and light switches after turning them off.
data[14][text]: 15. I need things to be arranged in a particular way.
data[15][text]: 16. I feel that there are good and bad numbers.
data[16][text]: 17. I wash my hands more often and longer than necessary.
data[17][text]: 18. I frequently get nasty thoughts and have difficulty in getting rid of them.
